> I saw in you patch that you are using `noundef` for arguments in tests, and without that, transformation is not working. Do you know why is that so?

`getConstantRangeAtUse` requires `noundef`. There is the comment:
```C++
// If the value is undef, a different value may be chosen in
// the select condition and at use.
if (!isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(SI->getCondition(), AC))
        break;
```
Some at-use transforms may be unsafe with undef values. I think it may be OK in this issue, but LVI Analysis does not provide such option.
